3. acceptance criteria coverage

- Public shell chrome now uses a dedicated public mode in [layouts.ex](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/lib/eboss_web/components/layouts.ex) with product-native nav framing, shared footer chrome, and a reusable CTA frame instead of generic marketing-shell patterns.
- Navigation and CTA framing were unified by wiring home and all public auth routes through the same `shell_mode="public"` and `current_path` contract in [home_live.ex](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/lib/eboss_web/live/home_live.ex) and the public auth LiveViews.
- Footer and shell elements now stay attached to the same panel, badge, nav-pill, and token vocabulary as the rest of the system through [patterns.css](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/assets/css/system/patterns.css).
- Desktop/mobile behavior is covered by the new responsive shell/footer/CTA CSS and the executable smoke coverage in [public_shell_smoke_test.exs](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/test/eboss_web/live/public_shell_smoke_test.exs) for `/`, `/sign-in`, `/register`, and `/forgot-password`.
- Theme/density coherence is preserved by building the new shell pieces on existing shared tokens and by extending the design-contract coverage in [design_surface_test.exs](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/test/design_surface_test.exs).

4. blockers/assumptions

- `mix precommit` could not be left passing in this sandbox. The blocker is external to the code change: child-app test aliases try to create/connect to `EBoss.Repo`, and all socket access to Postgres is denied here with `:eperm`.
- I added fuller repo-backed public shell assertions in [auth_live_test.exs](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/test/eboss_web/live/auth/auth_live_test.exs), but I could not execute that file end-to-end for the same database reason.
- A temporary `/tmp/codex-bin/mix` wrapper was used only to bypass Mix PubSub/lock socket restrictions in this environment; it is not part of the repository.
